268
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Besides, you're the bravest one of us.

269
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Sure.

270
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
I know you don't think that, but I don't care.

271
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Awaken, Nefertiti!

272
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,000
Awaken!

273
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Awaken, Nefertiti!

274
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,000
Awaken!

275
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Awaken, Nefertiti!

276
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,000
Awaken!

277
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,000
Hello, you bandaged wretches.

278
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Let's get this over with.

279
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,000
Kara Kedi.

280
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Catch them!

281
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Is this really your fastest?

282
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Wait.

283
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,000
This feels like a trap.

284
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Great.

285
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
You've just witnessed another incredible move from Uğur Böceği.

286
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Thanks for saving me.

287
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,000
No problem.

288
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,000
But it's not over yet.

289
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:22,000
First... First, Uğur Böceği needs to destroy the akuma in her earrings and fix everything.

290
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,000
I'm careful.

291
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,000
The earrings.

292
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:27,000
You thought well.

293
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,000
That was great, Uğur Böceği.

294
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,000
No.

295
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,000
You won't win this time, Uğur Böceği.

296
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
Help, Uğur Böceği!

297
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Crush that bug!

298
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,000
Uğur Böceği!

299
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,000
What's this?

300
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,000
Kara Kedi, this way!

301
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:24,000
We need to save Alya before she reaches the dark circle.

302
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,000
You cannot stop me from bringing Nefertiti back.

303
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,000
I will destroy you.

304
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Bring me my Anubis mummies.

305
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:44,000
Grant me the wings of Horus.

306
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Kara Kedi, on the earring.

307
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,000
The reading is right there.

308
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,000
Sekhmet, grant me your power.

309
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,000
It's over.

310
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,000
Uğur Böceği, save me!

311
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,000
Ra!

312
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,000
God of the sun!

313
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Accept this humble sacrifice and return my princess to me!

314
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Lucky Charm!

315
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,000
A Uğur Böceği costume?

316
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,000
This is our last resort?

317
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,000
This sacrifice is not enough for Nefertiti.

318
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,000
Hey, thank you.

319
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Too late, Uğur Böceği, the ritual has already begun.

320
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,000
Wait, let Alya go and sacrifice me instead.

321
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Wouldn't that be sweet revenge?

322
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:59,000
After all, I was the one who took Nefertiti from you five thousand years ago.

323
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:05,000
You would certainly make a much better sacrifice than this mortal.

324
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Horus, grant me your wings.

325
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,000
What?

326
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Are you serious?

327
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,000
Excuse me.

328
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:22,000
But she would have been a much better sacrifice than me.

329
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,000
Go ahead, Miraculous.

330
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,000
The earrings.

331
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
You win, Pharaoh.

332
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,000
You want my Miraculous?

333
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,000
Here you go.

334
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Catch.

335
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,000
A toy.

336
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,000
You tricked me.

337
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,000
You can't do evil anymore, little akuma.

338
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
Let the evil pass.

339
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
That's it.

340
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
Goodbye, little butterfly.

341
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:10,000
Miraculous Uğur Böceği.

342
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,000
What happened?

343
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Thanks, Uğur Böceği.

344
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,000
But I'm curious.

345
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Really... How old are you?

346
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,000
I'm too old to be a high school student.

347
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,000
That's for sure.

348
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
Aren't you curious about my age?

349
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Don't worry.

350
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
I'll be able to figure that out myself soon.

351
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,000
Where have you been?

352
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,000
You won't believe it, I got mummified.

353
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:57,000
I hope you weren't one of those trying to sacrifice me to Nefertiti.

354
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Terrible.

355
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,000
What?

356
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,000
You were being sacrificed?

357
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:06,000
If it weren't for you, I'd never have learned that Uğur Böceği is almost 5000 years old.

358
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,000
That's what friendship is all about.

359
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,000
But I still don't understand.

360
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,000
What was she doing with that 10th grade history book?

361
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:18,000
Maybe she wanted to learn what happened in the last 50 to 100 years that she missed.

362
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,000
You're probably right.

363
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
It must be hard to keep up.

364
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,000
Hey!

365
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,000
Uğur Böceği's book is gone!

366
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,000
You may have escaped this time.

367
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:36,000
But rest assured, one day, wherever you are, I will get your Miraculous.

368
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
You will become nothing.

369
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Nothing.

370
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,000
I don't understand.

371
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
I know I'm not 5000 years old.

372
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Then who was that Uğur Böceği on the papyrus?

373
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:54,000
There have always been kwamis like me and Uğur Böcekleri like you, right?

374
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,000
So that wasn't you on the papyrus either?

375
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,000
What did you think?

376
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:02,000
You don't look 5000 years old.

377
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,000
I'm not.

378
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,000
I'm even older.

379
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Because I'm the only kwami who has seen every Uğur Böceği since the beginning.

380
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,000
So there have been Uğur Böcekleri even clumsier than me, right?

381
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Every Uğur Böceği was different.

382
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Yes, I'm sure they were.

383
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Marinette, you are different.

384
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,000
But you have an interesting difference.

385
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,000
You're full of surprises and brave.

386
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,000
You're very talented.

387
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,000
You learn quickly.

388
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,000
Really?

389
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Yes.

390
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Yes.

391
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,000
I think it's okay now.

392
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,000
Don't forget, you have your history exam tomorrow.

393
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,000
Oh, right.